<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-688-335  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 688 335.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Dec 17 1990 v7 n50 p67(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IS client/server computing's 'killer app' near? (forms processing)(editorial)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Whitmore, Sam.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Client/Server ArchitectureForms ManagementMicrocomputersLocal Area NetworksData Base ServersTrendsFuture of Computing.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>When asked recently why client/server computing hasn't fully caught on yet,Intel CEO Andrew Grove answered that there doesn't yet exist a &quot;killerapplication&quot; that would capture corporate imaginations, thus making thetransition from terminal-host computing worthwhile.andM;With the right combination of engineering and marketing, that pivotalapplication just might be forms processing.andM;Thus far, forms processing hasn't really caught on, largely because thecategory itself is too diffused for the general public to understand.andP;  At thelow end, most word processors can act as forms processors by creating text,drawing and shading lines, and printing out the resulting document.andP;  A cutabove word processors are easy-to-use, HyperCardlike forms processors thatlet users type data into predesigned templates and print them out simply andinexpensively.andM;Then there are the high-end forms processors.andP;  Xerox Desktop Software'sFormBase can create forms that are linked to a powerful, complex, relationaldatabase.andP;  Delrina Technology is taking the interoperability approach withPerForm Designer and Filler for Digital Research's GEM, as well as for Mac,Windows and OS/2.andP;  Delrina offers a server and a client component, as doesIndigo Software with its JetForm products.andM;None of these products, however, has been engineered to work with PC-basedclient/server networks and distributed databases, such as Oracle Server forOS/2, or Microsoft's SQL Server.andP;  Until they are, forms processing won't makebig money for vendors, or solve big problems for users.andM;Businesses that have ongoing contact with customers are perfect candidatesfor forms-processing software.andP;  Generating character-based dBASE reportscould become a lot easier with the point-and-click, template qualities offorms processing.andM;Forms-processing vendors should align themselves with database-server firmslike Sybase Inc., Oracle and Gupta Technologies.andP;  Co-marketing deals wouldbenefit all parties and would help corporations embrace the cost-efficient,powerful future that is client/server computing.andO;</TEXT></DOC>